5ff5beef-e1d1-42a6-84c7-3f2fdff268c9	bcbae246-1638-492d-b281-eaac5dbdf747	inbound	workspace-noreply@google.com	The Google Workspace Team	richardson@superkabe.com	\N	[Product Update] New Workspace Intelligence admin controls for Google Workspace starting Apr 22, 2026	\r\n<!doctype html public "- / / w3c / / dtd html 4.01 transitional / / en" "http: / / www.w3.org / tr / html4 / loose.dtd">\r\n\r\n<html>\r\n<head></head>\r\n<body bgcolor=#f8f9fa style="width: 100%; margin:0; padding:0 !important; background-color: #f8f9fa;">\r\n<center style="width: 100%; table-layout: fixed;">\r\n\r\n<!--START OF MAIN CONTAINER-->\r\n<table align=center bgcolor=#FFFFFF border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style="max-width:600px; width:600px; Margin: 0 auto; " width=600>\r\n<!--START OF CONTENT CONTAINER-->\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=center bgcolor=#ffffff class=mktoContainer id=content_container style="background-color: #ffffff; " valign=top>\r\n  \r\n<!--LOGO CONTAINER-->\r\n<table align=center border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style="max-width:600px; width:100%; background: #f8f9fa; " width=600>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n  \r\n<td height=80 style="padding:0 24px 0 30px; height: 80px; vertical-align: middle; text-align: left" valign=middle>\r\n  <!--Change this logo accordingly baseD on the MSA requirement-->\r\n<span style="font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #000000;"> </span>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 22px; padding-bottom: 6px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #dcdcdc; border-bottom-width: 1px" width=100%><span style="font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #000000;"><img alt="Google Workspace logo" border=0 src=http://services.google.com/fh/files/emails/google_workspace_750x96px_gray_lockup_google_product_624x96px_clr.png style="display: block;" title=Google width=250> </span></div>\r\n<span style="font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #000000;"> <!-- This is the beginning of the subject --> </span> <!-- GOOGLE WORKSPACE (KEEP/DELETE AS NECESSARY) -->\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<!-- END OF LOGO CONTAINER-->\r\n<!--START OF PREHEADER-->\r\n\r\n<!-- Include the Pre-header snippet, copy HTML from TEMPLATE SNIPPET ID 9160213 and add the pre-header text-->\r\n<div style="height:0px; font-size:0px; max-height:0px; min-height: 0px; line-height:0px; width: 100%; color: #fff; display:none;">Review new Workspace Intelligence features and admin settings.</div>\r\n<!--END OF PREHEADER-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table align=center border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mktoModule id=bodyCopyModule role=presentation style="max-width:600px; width:100%;" width=600>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n\r\n<td style="font-family: Roboto,Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px; color: #3C4043; margin: 0; padding: 0; text-align: left; padding:8px 50px 8px 50px;" valign=top>\r\n\r\n<!--START OF MSA ADMIN MESSAGE-->\r\n  \r\n   <!-- NON-INCIDENT MSAS (KEEP/DELETE AS NECESSARY) -->\r\n\r\n<p>Dear administrator,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You’re receiving this communication because we’re introducing <strong>Workspace Intelligence</strong>. Workspace Intelligence is an underlying AI system that provides <strong>Gemini</strong> with a real-time understanding of your work across <strong>Google Workspace</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Workspace Intelligence, all of your generative AI tasks within Workspace will be grounded in your Workspace data across <strong>Gmail</strong>, <strong>Chat</strong>, <strong>Calendar</strong>, and <strong>Drive</strong>, eliminating the need for users to manually provide context to Gemini on every query.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, imagine you want to draft an update to your manager on “Project X” in <strong>Google Docs</strong>. You simply ask Gemini in Docs. Workspace Intelligence will consult all relevant data, your meeting notes, documentation, and chat discussions about Project X, and draft the report in seconds, with full citations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As an administrator, you have control over which data sources Workspace Intelligence can use for your organization. We understand this change may require some adjustments and have provided additional information below to guide you through these new controls.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What this means for your organization</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Workspace Intelligence securely draws from content in Gmail, Drive, Chat, and Calendar, as well as connected third party sources, to deliver personalized outputs via Gemini 3 reasoning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting <strong>April 22, 2026</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>New Admin Controls:</strong> You will have access to new controls in the Admin console to manage which data sources are used to ground Workspace Intelligence. <strong>Note:</strong> it may take up to 3 days after rollout begins for these controls to appear.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Default Setting:</strong> The Workspace Intelligence settings will be default <strong>ON</strong> for all users in your organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What’s not changing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These changes do not alter our underlying data handling practices or <a target=_blank href=https://c.gle/ADMV5J84jmNORvCNnlJi7Qii6vb5XAPJvGjZbrjMhumUK5OQtR684hNE8Sc_1Pi1GFLxjFBa2yDAplhl3P4SDmUW32ToHUB7Midn95qINCOgEN_CzP7BomB1vypNOlw1kSKdVPxlNNQ1DtE3hVWj-HsCKCLrl-2xXsWk1G6tksboWmtv_C4Nzv5LgDdcMTaZM2HjaJSnoWEeyUOSxNwiJy1yl1e5EcJ0QZQ>privacy commitments</a>. AI features respect user-level content access, ensuring that responses are grounded only in content that a user already has permission to view. <strong>Your data is never used to train generative AI models or for advertising purposes</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Additional Details:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Workspace Intelligence powers AI capabilities, such as AI Overviews in Gmail and Drive, and Help me create in Docs, by securely accessing content across Gmail, Drive, and Calendar.</li>\r\n  <li>New Admin console settings will allow admins to decide at the organizational unit and group level which data sources (Gmail, Chat, Calendar, or Drive) may be actively searched by Gemini features in Workspace.</li>\r\n  <li>If enabled, the AI features respect user-level content access, ensuring that responses are grounded only in content owned by or shared with that user.</li>\r\n  <li>If you turn off Workspace Intelligence for a specific data source, generative AI features will not actively search for content from the disabled source. However, if a user adds a specific source to their prompt, that source will be used in Gemini&#39;s response.\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>For example, if you turn Drive off as a source, users can still ask Gemini about specific files. Gemini will consult these files, but it won&#39;t actively search for other files. Additionally, if you turn off certain data sources, users may lose access to specific AI features.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What you need to do</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>No action is required unless you’d like to change the default settings. To modify the Workspace Intelligence Admin settings, follow the steps in this <a target=_blank href=https://c.gle/ADMV5J-G8oHGI0tgZeoIHlNIn2D4-mJG7-zjp8LIwavT4w4bpQqN_1biD7MZnyXlO65rqUG1PMtVJM142H9tOTpiERGC9tVAE1tpV4S-VCunEa__228io-Z_8E-EjOKu2GBq7pne-jl-yVv3pg>Help Center article</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>We’re here to help</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have questions, please review the Help Center article linked to above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks for choosing Google Workspace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>– The Google Workspace Team</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--END OF MSA ADMIN MESSAGE-->\r\n</td>\r\n  \r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--START OF FEEDBACK FORM-->\r\n<!-- Include the Customer feedback form snippet, copy HTML from TEMPLATE SNIPPET ID coco/7501725 and add relevant links -->\r\n<table style=width:100%;border:1px;>\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td colspan=2 style=text-align:center; width=100%><strong style="font-size:14px; color:#919599ff;">Was this information helpful?</strong></td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td style=text-align:center;><a href=https://c.gle/ADMV5J96j-hdrG43h9J3VyAy1KOxPsX2Vjl_dSpwOwsKzg0hMGYXVtn-k-TJb695VOy00r8ZklsVQabLy6D6QDyUt1w6QgJD7pwgrN5lNpll62HXVbpCSYXrlAs_KULzkalldJSJefjRTyC8LyuUVIzUGuD7fyUVkwTOtY_EFJ2af0P4IIJIF63qiup7BQLRL_CU7r1NLr81wE37tQfqVa9_1fUYecFKFHvegTlmVRMS2xWIC6SwTfzVZ7AbpCSUEzRvCg style="color:#1a73e8; font-family:Roboto, arial; font-size:14px; text-decoration:none" target=_blank><img alt="A smiling face" src=https://services.google.com/fh/files/emails/happy_emojis.png style="-ms-interpolation-mode:bicubic; border:none; outline:none; text-decoration:none; padding-top: 1px;" width=30> </a>     <a href=https://c.gle/ADMV5J-vkcqnTdWb9gd_OjdwDnJRxRfbdFG-cbpLnjULC5gDdODZHR1a3-D-lQSiXhZYxe6j4N9-ATJxRrYPnNIAxHORxVRtfrGNUXGT0MCoXDDcnl_h6utEss2o9nx8j-MDQIGDhf9WCbnrEjBVjWy0tP5ouMZ9gWZoZYbRyHfl14cOYTsMjDb1L7q9Np9V5ibQ9ZU5T8cM_qRrH2qSVqGnFSIfGKJo73jr7v1mtcKA34dWJ1tuZfYnB8Xh9HX1HS0EoAcUk_o style="color:#1a73e8; font-family:Roboto, arial; font-size:14px; text-decoration:none" target=_blank><img alt="A neutral face" src=https://services.google.com/fh/files/emails/neutral_emojis.png style="-ms-interpolation-mode:bicubic; border:none; outline:none; text-decoration:none" width=30> </a>     <a href=https://c.gle/ADMV5J_ExQG4zQBVWTjC8S_WZn1vlLwIm9Q2h2CafrEfTDFLRVd7PNlL-5pOIK3jyi8jKXspybN7Dfx3rx9w2LltEiAX1I4v1dxbENjy9A7qyEdUw5Sjg4SAdcrgTCmsuh3Nto2NuWJ6G2nbGkNTQOnRfqmiA1gDu3rdBPxeldbqhMv7OANYmmIARXkdLU8HBaLDwZiKKJ5ZWYuICcnhODH4M29tbwa-elICdkmmaLCq-SbXSti9srlneZxYJAfsWZZo style="color:#1a73e8; font-family:Roboto, arial; font-size:14px; text-decoration:none" target=_blank><img alt="A sad face" src=https://services.google.com/fh/files/emails/sad_emojis.png style="-ms-interpolation-mode:bicubic; border:none; outline:none; text-decoration:none" width=30></a></td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<!--END OF FEEDBACK FORM-->\r\n  \r\n<div>\