eight=48 src=https://services.google.com/fh/files/misc/linkedin_grey_a11y.png style="height: 48px;"></a></td>\r\n<td style="width: 48px; padding-left: 8px; font-family: Roboto,Arial,sans-serif;" width=48><a href=https://c.gle/ADMV5J8C9pcN4PW-CkONhqAvsYdn04vrmXRdRLmAj960Oc7BA5iRM8Qxb5rozWtJgWY2POz7oAswJWy0qFABvQ9JA5cLHN30uvt0gYOlBUgEYsd4U2AL0DtYPNPgAWBlP55GTKiaDdA><img alt=YouTube border=0 height=48 src=https://services.google.com/fh/files/misc/youtube_grey_a11y.png style="height: 48px;"></a>\r\n</td>\r\n<!--END OF SOCIALS-->\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<!--END OF CONTENT CONTAINER-->\r\n</table>\r\n<!--END OF MAIN CONTAINER-->\r\n</center>\r\n<img alt="" height=1 width=3 src=https://notifications.google.com/g/img/ADMV5J_2RgwJYCiLIl2gmmwqL_SaymegmCqgD1CimpI9IM5sPUxrWqBUkhOlXRDNQ_4d0lgKZrO4VSDOjATdEhnxfRlz7kcB1fp5bpT6QGTA-lC2ISDbIoZ1PFX7Wm7v0Us5X2Y3Ow.gif></body>\r\n</html>\r\n	Google Workspace logo\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nReview new Workspace Intelligence features and admin settings.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDear administrator,\r\n\r\nYou're receiving this communication because we're introducing Workspace  \r\nIntelligence. Workspace Intelligence is an underlying AI system that  \r\nprovides Gemini with a real-time understanding of your work across Google  \r\nWorkspace.\r\n\r\nWith Workspace Intelligence, all of your generative AI tasks within  \r\nWorkspace will be grounded in your Workspace data across Gmail, Chat,  \r\nCalendar, and Drive, eliminating the need for users to manually provide  \r\ncontext to Gemini on every query.\r\n\r\nFor example, imagine you want to draft an update to your manager on  \r\n“Project X” in Google Docs. You simply ask Gemini in Docs. Workspace  \r\nIntelligence will consult all relevant data, your meeting notes,  \r\ndocumentation, and chat discussions about Project X, and draft the report  \r\nin seconds, with full citations.\r\n\r\nAs an administrator, you have control over which data sources Workspace  \r\nIntelligence can use for your organization. We understand this change may  \r\nrequire some adjustments and have provided additional information below to  \r\nguide you through these new controls.\r\n\r\nWhat this means for your organization\r\n\r\nWorkspace Intelligence securely draws from content in Gmail, Drive, Chat,  \r\nand Calendar, as well as connected third party sources, to deliver  \r\npersonalized outputs via Gemini 3 reasoning.\r\n\r\nStarting April 22, 2026:\r\n\r\n\r\nNew Admin Controls: You will have access to new controls in the Admin  \r\nconsole to manage which data sources are used to ground Workspace  \r\nIntelligence. Note: it may take up to 3 days after rollout begins for these  \r\ncontrols to appear.\r\nDefault Setting: The Workspace Intelligence settings will be default ON for  \r\nall users in your organization.\r\n\r\nWhat's not changing:\r\n\r\nThese changes do not alter our underlying data handling practices or  \r\nprivacy commitments. AI features respect user-level content access,  \r\nensuring that responses are grounded only in content that a user already  \r\nhas permission to view. Your data is never used to train generative AI  \r\nmodels or for advertising purposes.\r\n\r\nAdditional Details:\r\n\r\n\r\nWorkspace Intelligence powers AI capabilities, such as AI Overviews in  \r\nGmail and Drive, and Help me create in Docs, by securely accessing content  \r\nacross Gmail, Drive, and Calendar.\r\nNew Admin console settings will allow admins to decide at the  \r\norganizational unit and group level which data sources (Gmail, Chat,  \r\nCalendar, or Drive) may be actively searched by Gemini features in  \r\nWorkspace.\r\nIf enabled, the AI features respect user-level content access, ensuring  \r\nthat responses are grounded only in content owned by or shared with that  \r\nuser.\r\nIf you turn off Workspace Intelligence for a specific data source,  \r\ngenerative AI features will not actively search for content from the  \r\ndisabled source. However, if a user adds a specific source to their prompt,  \r\nthat source will be used in Gemini's response.\r\n\r\nFor example, if you turn Drive off as a source, users can still ask Gemini  \r\nabout specific files. Gemini will consult these files, but it won't  \r\nactively search for other files. Additionally, if you turn off certain data  \r\nsources, users may lose access to specific AI features.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat you need to do\r\n\r\nNo action is required unless you'd like to change the default settings. To  \r\nmodify the Workspace Intelligence Admin settings, follow the steps in this  \r\nHelp Center article.\r\n\r\nWe're here to help\r\n\r\nIf you have questions, please review the Help Center article linked to  \r\nabove.\r\n\r\nThanks for choosing Google Workspace.\r\n\r\n– The Google Workspace Team\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWas this information helpful?\r\n\r\nA smiling face A neutral face A sad face\r\n\r\n\r\n© 2026 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043\r\n\r\nYou have received this important update about your Google Workspace account  \r\nbecause you designated this email address as a primary or secondary contact  \r\nfor mandatory service communications in your Google Admin console profile.\r\n\r\n\r\nTwitter Facebook LinkedIn YouTube\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	<2e853541bad5db27a0bcd9257363b395a81cc984-20401107-111841305@google.com>	\N	\N	f	f	2026-04-23 01:54:56	2026-04-23 01:55:08.913
